28 September 2011 Government Communication and Information System (GCIS) will host the first Public Sector Manager Forum. The Forum will be addressed by the Minister of Health, Dr Aaron Motsoaledi. The discussions will focus mainly on the National Policy on National Health Insurance (NHI) as approved by Cabinet. The Forum is held in support of the monthly Public Sector Magazine published by GCIS. The purpose is to provide public service managers with a platform to thoroughly engage with policy makers in order to broaden their understanding and enhance the impact of implementation. Members of the media are invited to attend as follows: Date: Thursday, 29 September 2011 Time: 17h00 19h00 Venue: Sheraton Hotel (Pretoria) RSVP by email or sms to E-mail: Pheliswa@gcis.gov.za Cell: 082 413 4609 Enquiries: Jimmy Manyi Cell: 082 379 3454 Issued by: Government Communication and Information System